HEADWORD: Osteoblast
<hw>Os"te*o*blast</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Osteo-</ets> + <ets>-blast</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>One of the protoplasmic cells which occur in the osteogenetic layer
of the periosteum, and from or around which the matrix of the bone is
developed; an osteoplast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>osteoclasis</ent>⟦br⟧
